ArcticDownloader 0.1.8 update log

Purpose:
- Track code changes made in the Linux workspace so they can be mirrored in the Windows workspace.

Format:
- Date
- Change summary
- Files changed
- Notes

Entries:
- 2026-03-16
  - Fixed Linux Intel XPU readiness checks so they no longer require the `video` group to report the runtime as ready.
  - Files changed:
    - Cargo.toml
    - src-tauri/Cargo.toml
    - src-tauri/src/main.rs
    - version0.1.8_updates
  - Notes:
    - The Intel XPU status check now treats the `render` group as required and the `video` group as optional.
    - This prevents users from getting stuck on a repeated "log out/login or reboot" message after restart when Intel XPU is otherwise ready.
- 2026-03-16
  - Created a human-readable changelog file for version 0.1.8.
  - Files changed:
    - CHANGELOG_0.1.8.md
    - version0.1.8_updates
  - Notes:
    - The changelog is written in short release-note style and documents the Linux Intel XPU readiness-check fix.
- 2026-03-17
  - Refined the Linux Intel XPU readiness check to verify actual render-node access instead of only checking group names.
  - Files changed:
    - src-tauri/src/main.rs
    - version0.1.8_updates
  - Notes:
    - The Intel XPU status check now inspects `/dev/dri/renderD*` access directly and uses current-session group detection more robustly.
    - This should stop false 'log out/login or reboot' warnings on systems where Intel render access is already available.
